/*1.DOM concept
      
     The Document Object Model (DOM) is a programming interface for HTML(HyperText Markup Language) 
     and XML(Extensible markup language) documents. It defines the logical structure of 
     documents and the way a document is accessed and manipulated.

Example: In this example, We use HTML element id to find the DOM HTML element.*/

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
 
<body>
    <h2>Sri krishna college of technoloy</h2>
 
    <!-- Finding the HTML Elements by their Id in DOM -->
    <p id="intro">A Computer Science portal for students.</p>
    <p>This example illustrates the <b>getElementById</b> method.</p>
    <p id="demo"></p>
    <script>
        const element = document.getElementById("intro");
        document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML =
          "GeeksforGeeks introduction is: " + element.innerHTML;
    </script>
</body>
 
</html>

